  "role": "2.3.4 cross-timeframe alignment (setup-level; no fourth OHLCV parquet) — computed from the already-resolved 1h base + causal as-of 1d/1w context",
  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Machine registry + KNOWLEDGE BASE for the 2.3.4 between_timeframes namespace (Feature IDs 900..999). standard_trendline_features = FT900..FT908 (always ON when the stage is enabled): cross-timeframe alignment of the 8 base FT + a direction consensus. additional_features = F909..F999. Every feature declares its reducer + source_feature_requirements (feature->feature edges); the runtime gathers each edge's value across feature-LOCALLY available + fresh source timeframes and applies REDUCERS[reducer]. >= min_available_sources required else NaN (no imputation; the setup is never dropped). Runtime parses this JSON; the Markdown docs are human-only.",
    "doc": "Features/features_between_timeframes/README.md",
    "sot": "Layers_Short_SOT/ENG/Layer2_3_add_features_to_standard_trendlines_features_eng.md",
    "rule": "A source timeframe is valid FOR A FEATURE only when it is a selected source, its context is fresh (age <= max_source_age_hours), AND every edge value that feature needs for that TF is finite. Cross-TF features carry NO availability value into X; the between_timeframes_available_* audit columns (outside X) record general context availability."
  },
